3EFailures%20leave%20Russia%20reliant%20on%20older%20missiles%20that%20won't%20last%20forever%2C%20experts%20warn.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20the%20world's%20largest%20nuclear%20arsenal%2C%20but%20it's%20having%20trouble%20getting%20its%20newest%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missile%20to%20work.%20The%20debacle%20leaves%20it%20dependent%20on%20capable%20but%20inferior%20missiles%20at%20a%20time%20when%20other%20major%20powers%20are%20modernizing%20their%20nuclear%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20new%20RS-28%20Sarmat%20ICBM%20appeared%20to%20suffer%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-icbm-test-fail-hints-at-new-missile-problems-analysts-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecatastrophic%20failure%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20testing%20in%20September%2C%20with%20satellite%20imagery%20showing%20a%20big%20crater%20around%20the%20launchpad%20at%20the%20Plesetsk%20Cosmodrome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20apparent%20failure%20followed%20what%20missile%20experts%20have%20described%20as%20a%20host%20of%20other%20issues.%20Ejection%20tests%20and%20its%20flight%20testing%20were%20repeatedly%20delayed%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rusi.org%2Fexplore-our-research%2Fpublications%2Fcommentary%2Frussias-sarmat-test-failure-implications-strategic-balance%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%20think%20tank%20in%20London%2C%20and%20it%20had%20at%20least%20two%20canceled%20flight%20tests%20and%20at%20least%20one%20other%20flight%20test%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Sarmat%20is%20meant%20to%20replace%20the%20Soviet-era%20R-36%2C%20which%20first%20entered%20service%20in%201988.%20NATO%20calls%20the%20long-range%20missile%2C%20which%20has%20been%20modified%20over%20the%20years%2C%20the%20SS-18%20%26quot%3BSatan.%26quot%3B%20Without%20the%20new%20Sarmat%2C%20Russia%20has%20to%20rely%20on%20older%20missiles%2C%20extending%20their%20lives%2C%20but%20that%20can't%20go%20on%20indefinitely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229d91baa2-083b-4da8-a8dc-3564db95933b%5C%22%3EStuck%20with%20inferior%20missiles%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDelays%20to%20the%20Sarmat%2C%20or%20even%20its%20cancellation%2C%20would%20mean%20Russia%20has%20to%20keep%20using%20older%20systems%20as%20nations%20like%20China%20field%20new%20DF-41%20ICBMs%20and%20the%20US%20pushes%20forward%20with%20upgrades%20for%20its%20ICBM%20force%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Sentinel%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20R-36%20is%20%26quot%3Balready%20really%2C%20really%20past%20its%20service%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Timothy%20Wright%2C%20a%20missile%20technology%20expert%20at%20the%20International%20Institute%20for%20Strategic%20Studies%2C%20yet%20the%20Russians%20keep%20having%20to%20extend%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20said%20at%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20century%20they%20were%20going%20to%20be%20out%20of%20service%20by%202007%2C%20but%20here%20they%20are%2C%20still%20in%20operation%20nearly%20two%20decades%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20only%20so%20much%20they%20can%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20said.%20%26quot%3BParts%20will%20start%20failing%20at%20some%20point.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20the%20R-36s%20%26quot%3Bwill%20eventually%20start%20failing%20because%20their%20parts%20just%20will%20need%20replacement%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20make%20the%20parts%20anymore.%26quot%3B%20If%20Moscow%20tried%20to%20launch%2040%20R-36s%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20might%20not%20get%20all%2040%20out%20the%20ground%2C%20frankly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20Sarmat%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missil%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63f62f5e88f76900192cd176%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22822%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussia's%20Sarmat%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missile%20is%20launched%20in%20Russia's%20northwest%20region%20of%20Plesetsk%20in%20April%202022.%3Cp%3ERoscosmos%20Space%20Agency%20Press%20Service%20via%20AP%2C%20File%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFabian%20Hoffmann%2C%20a%20missile%20expert%20at%20the%20Oslo%20Nuclear%20Project%2C%20said%20the%20R-36%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bsitting%20there%20for%20a%20really%20long%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20was%20required%20to%20reduce%20the%20size%20of%20its%20arsenal%20of%20missiles%20under%20the%20New%20START%20treaty%20with%20the%20US.%20Hoffman%20said%20that%20Russia%20could%20use%20old%20parts%20from%20those%20missiles%20to%20keep%20its%20usable%20ones%20running.%20But%20the%20supply%20is%20not%20infinite%2C%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWho%20knows%20how%20much%20these%20missiles%20can%20still%20take%2C%20how%20many%20years%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20the%20possibility%20Russia%20would%20%26quot%3Bhave%20to%20start%20cannibalizing%20existing%20missiles%2C%20taking%20them%20out%20of%20service%20or%20retiring%20them%20or%20taking%20them%20off%20what%20they%20call%20combat%20duty%20alert%2C%20which%20is%20where%20the%20missile%20is%20literally%20ready%20to%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20other%20ICBMs%2C%20but%20the%20R-36%20carries%20the%20largest%20and%20most%20strategically%20significant%20payload.%20The%20Sarmat%2C%20as%20its%20replacement%2C%20will%20likewise%20carry%20a%20substantial%20payload.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c98c0ba2-0080-4768-8fd9-052109cb6939%5C%22%3EBig%20missiles%20with%20lots%20of%20warheads%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20purpose%20of%20the%20Sarmat%20was%20%26quot%3Bto%20constitute%20a%20big%20bulk%20of%20their%20warheads%20in%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20said.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20ICBM%20is%20a%20large%2C%20long-range%20weapon%20able%20to%20carry%20a%20heavy%20MIRV%20payload%2C%20meaning%20multiple%20independent%20re-entry%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Sarmat%20has%20an%20estimated%20maximum%20range%20of%2018%2C000%20miles.%20It%20has%20a%20ten-ton%20payload%20and%20can%20carry%2010%20large%20warheads%20or%2016%20smaller%20ones%2C%20per%20a%20Missile%20Threat%20fact%20sheet%20from%20the%20Center%20of%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies.%20The%20R-36%20it%20is%20meant%20to%20replace%20has%20a%20shorter%20range%20but%20similar%20payload%2C%20able%20to%20carry%2010%20multiple%20independent%20re-entry%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20large%20grey%20missile%20is%20seen%20on%20its%20side%20resting%20on%20supports%20above%20a%20tarmac%20and%20grass%20ground%20and%20a%20grey%20sky%20behind%20it%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678a946910c98eace912e138%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20disarmed%20R-36%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missile%2C%20which%20has%20the%20NATO%20reporting%20name%20SS-18%20Satan.%3Cp%3EMykhaylo%20Palinchak%2FSOPA%20Images%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20Russian%20ICBMs%20are%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20smaller%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20said.%20They%20can't%20carry%20the%20same%20heavy%20MIRV%20payload.%20Russia's%20RS-24%20Yars%20ICBM%2C%20for%20example%2C%20can%20only%20carry%20three%20MIRV%20warheads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20May%202023%2C%20Russia%20had%201%2C674%20warheads%20deployed%2C%20with%20a%20total%20stockpile%20of%204%2C489%2C%20per%20the%20CSIS.%20Many%20of%20these%20are%20deployed%20on%20other%20missiles%20and%20elements%20of%20the%20Russian%20nuclear%20triad%2C%20which%20provide%20it%20with%20deterrence%2C%20but%20Russia%20wants%20the%20big%20missile%20with%20the%20tremendous%20destructive%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmissilethreat.csis.org%2Fmissile%2Fss-18%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderstood%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20have%2046%20R-36s%20in%20April%202016.%20Wright%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bif%20they%20then%20took%20that%20missile%20out%20of%20service%2C%20then%20they%20have%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20gap.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20for%20Russia%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20ensure%20they%20have%20warhead%20parity%20with%20the%20Americans%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhatever%20number%20the%20Americans%20have%2C%20the%20Russians%20want%20it%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20appears%20to%20be%20keeping%20its%20warheads%20limited%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20New%20START%20treaty.%20But%20if%20that%20changes%2C%20and%20it%20may%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-threatens-last-major-nuclear-arms-treaty-new-start-us-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eas%20Russia%20has%20suspended%20its%20involvement%20with%20the%20treaty%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Russia%20may%20want%20to%20deploy%20more%20warheads.%20Without%20the%20Sarmat%2C%20Russia%20will%20need%20to%20find%20other%20places%20for%20its%20warheads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d96de3d8-22bb-4de9-93f4-5b454fbb4ccb%5C%22%3EThe%20Sarmat's%20problems%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHoffman%20said%20the%20most%20recent%20Sarmat%20test%20was%20%26quot%3Bcatastrophic.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bit's%20not%20even%20like%20the%20missile%20failed%20to%20hit%20its%20target%20and%20you%20can%20say%2C%20'Oh%2C%20the%20guidance%20system%20didn't%20really%20work.'%20No%2C%20the%20whole%20thing%20blew%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20it%20was%20either%20a%20freak%20accident%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20something%20fundamentally%20wrong%20with%20the%20propulsion%20system%2C%20which%20is%20of%20course%20catastrophic%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20if%20I%20was%20Russia%2C%20I%20think%20at%20this%20point%20I%20would%20be%20concerned%20about%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20experts%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcepa.org%2Farticle%2Frussias-satanic-failure-opens-the-door-to-nato-rethink%2F%5C%22%20t