F6786cb02e294a7514e8d19fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22844%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20average%20NFCC%20client%20was%20estimated%20to%20be%20in%20Stage%206%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20of%202024%2C%20a%20severe%20form%20of%20debt%20distress%20that%20involves%20cutting%20out%20essentials.%3Cp%3ENational%20Foundation%20for%20Credit%20Counseling%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trend%20of%20higher%20debt%20distress%20looks%20poised%20to%20continue%20through%202025%2C%20the%20firm%20said%20in%20its%20latest%20Financial%20Stress%20Forecast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBruce%20McClary%2C%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20membership%20and%20communications%20at%20the%20NFCC%2C%20said%20that%20he%20was%20seeing%20more%20people%20make%20sacrifices%20to%20service%20their%20credit%20card%20loans%2C%20such%20as%20by%20borrowing%20against%20their%20home%20or%20their%20401(k).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20particular%2C%20he's%20expecting%20a%20surge%20of%20debt-distressed%20consumers%20to%20come%20in%20for%20help%20in%20the%20next%20three%20months%2C%20as%20Americans%20face%20bills%20coming%20due%20from%20the%20holidays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20expecting%20these%20levels%20of%20stress%20to%20reach%20a%20level%20significantly%20higher%20than%20anything%20we've%20seen%20over%20the%20past%20four%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3Bl%20think%20it%20would%20be%20also%20true%20to%20say%20that%20we're%20expecting%20it%20to%20go%20beyond%20what%20we%20saw%20pre-pandemic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c3acc511-ca7c-4ee9-a24b-d4ec656012ad%5C%22%3ECredit%20card%20nation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20are%20leaning%20on%20credit%20cards%20to%20get%20by%20more%20than%20ever.%20Household%20credit%20card%20balances%20surged%20to%20a%20record%20%241.17%20trillion%20as%20of%20the%20third%20quarter%20of%202024%2C%20up%20%24360%20billion%20from%20the%20third%20quarter%20of%202020%2C%20New%20York%20Fed%20data%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20increase%20was%20driven%20by%20a%20perfect%20storm%20of%20factors%2C%20McClary%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20how%20credit%20card%20companies%20loosened%20lending%20standards%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20accumulated%20effects%20of%20higher%20inflation.%20The%20higher%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20combined%20with%20the%20post-pandemic%20shopping%20boom%2C%20made%20consumers%20more%20likely%20to%20carry%20a%20balance%20from%20month%20to%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20those%20consumers%20are%20looking%20far%20worse%20than%20they%20did%20several%20years%20ago.%20Households%20likely%20depleted%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frbsf.org%2Fresearch-and-insights%2Fblog%2Fsf-fed-blog%2F2024%2F05%2F03%2Fpandemic-savings-are-gone-whats-next-for-us-consumers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexcess%20savings%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20pandemic%20by%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202024%2C%20according%20to%20an%20analysis%20from%20the%20San%20Francisco%20Fed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20credit%20card%20companies%20began%20rolling%20up%20their%20emergency%20forbearance%20programs%20in%202022%2C%20which%20were%20implemented%20to%20provide%20debt%20forgiveness%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20half%20of%20all%20credit%20card%20users%20said%20they%20carried%20a%20balance%20month-to-month%2C%20according%20to%20a%202024%20Bankrate%20survey%2C%20up%20from%2039%25%20of%20users%20who%20carried%20a%20balance%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20those%20who%20held%20credit%20card%20debt%2C%2029%25%20of%20users%20said%20they%20believed%20it%20would%20take%20them%20more%20than%205%20years%20to%20pay%20off%20their%20loans%2C%20while%206%25%20said%20they%20believed%20they%20would%20never%20be%20able%20to%20pay%20their%20dues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHeather%20Hunt%2C%20the%20director%20of%20Fitch%20Ratings%2C%20says%20she%20largely%20expects%20debt%20distress%20to%20rise%20as%20consumer%20finances%20continue%20to%20weaken%20in%202025%2C%20especially%20if%20the%20job%20market%20deteriorates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20short%20story%20is%20that%20if%20unemployment%20is%20rising%2C%20then%20your%20charge-offs%20are%20going%20to%20rise.%20And%20that%20just%20signals%20consumers%20are%20under%20more%20and%20more%20distress%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterest%20rates%20on%20credit%20card%20plans%20charged%20by%20commercial%20banks%20soared%20past%2021%25%20in%202024%2C%20the%20highest%20in%20at%20least%20three%20decades%2C%20according%20to%20Fed%20data%20dating%20back%20to%201994.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%2028%25%20of%20credit%20card%20debt%20holders%20said%20day-to-day%20expenses%2C%20like%20groceries%2C%20were%20the%20largest%20reason%20they%20carried%20their%20balances%20month%20to%20month%2C%20according%20to%20Bankrate's%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcClary%20says%20he%20advises%20people%20struggling%20with%20credit%20card%20debt%20to%20speak%20to%20a%20nonprofit%20credit%20counselor%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20falling%20behind%20on%20your%20payments%2C%20the%20delinquency%20interest%20rates%2C%20the%20penalty%20interest%20rates%20combined%20with%20the%20fees%2C%20could%20be%20the%20death%20blow%2C%26quot%3B%20McClary%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20just%20unsustainable%20for%20people%20who%20are%20already%20financially%20struggling%20and%20are%20living%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20struggling%20with%20credit%20card%20loans%2C%20a%20mortgage%2C%20or%20other%20forms%20of%20personal%20debt%3F%20Email%20this%20reporter%20to%20share%20your%20story%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajsor%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ejsor%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcredit-card-debt-payment-interest-rates-inflation-personal-finance-20